5) Expected phenotype: If this gene was knocked out of BCDO2 in chicken, it would result in a yellow pigmentation of the skin and adipose tissue. BCDO2 encodes an enzyme that spilts the carotenoids chicken consume. Without it, carotenoids would accumulate in their tissues rather than being broken down, producing a visible yellow coloration in the skin and fat that is normally white. 
